erson, smarter.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nConsistency is an under-appreciated inspirational quality. It’s that ability to conduct yourself in a consistent, reliable manner that others will respect and appreciate.\n\n- Del Suggs, Truly Leading: Lessons in Leadership\n|\nOne day, I shall explode like an artillery shell and all my bits will be found on the writing table.\n\n- Gustave\n|\nThere's Only so much emotional super glue in a person's soul, that everything just stays broken.\n\n- Laurell K. Hamilton, Incubus Dreams\n|\nGoing against the storm requires strength, energy and a will to succeed.\n\n- Mitta\n|\nYou need to find a way to live your life, that it doesn't make a mockery of your values.\n\n- Bill\n|\nThe same word we love and hate, leaves in different directions, taking different paths.\n\n- Dejan Stojanovic, The Sun Watches the Sun\n|\ndon't try to be best, try to give your best.\n\n- kurbhatt\n|\nFreedom is sloppy. But since tyranny's the only guaranteed byproduct of those who insist on a perfect world, freedom will have to do.\n\n- Bill Willingham, Fables: Werewolves of the Heartland\n|\nWhen God knows you're ready for the responsibility of commitment, He'll reveal the right person under the right circumstances.\n\n- Joshua Harris, I Kissed Dating Goodbye\n|\nBack then I could not understand one word of what I read.Reading did, however, give me heart. Even if you cannot understand what you are reading you can get something from books.\n\n- Peter\n|\nIf you want to rebel, rebel from inside the system.That's much more powerful than rebelling outside the system.\n\n- Marie Lu, Legend\n|\nThe power of God is with you at all times; through the activities of mind, senses, breathing, and emotions; and is constantly doing all the work using you as a mere instrument.\n\n- Anonymous, Bhagavad Gita: El Canto del Senor\n|\nIt's not objective. It's subjective.” Katya hooks her bra behind her back. “It's just what you think, not the truth.\n\n- E. Lockhart, Fly on the Wall: How One Girl Saw Everything\n|\nIf people call your work perceptible, be it in positive or negative terms, do ask them about what made them draw that conclusion.\n\n- Mohith\n|\nFor the wages of sin is Death, but the gift of God is everlasting Life in Christ Jesus or LORD.\n\n- Anonymous, Holy Bible: King James Version\n|\nHave we freed this man or cursed him?' he wondered aloud.'Freedom is never a curse, brother,' Thirty-four insisted. 'But it is often a hard road.\n\n- Anthony  Ryan, Queen of Fire\n|\nPleasure is the only thing one should live for, nothing ages like happiness.\n\n- Oscar\n|\nI shouldn't believe anything I say, if I were you-and that includes what I just told you.\n\n- Jasper Fforde, The Eyre Affair\n|\nWhat if I told you 10 years from now your life would be exactly the same?Doubt you'd be happy.So, why are you afraid of change?\n\n- Karen\n|\nWhat the caterpillar calls the end of the world, the master calls a butterfly.\n\n- Richard Bach, Illusions: The Adventures of a Reluctant Messiah\n|\nand I ask myself and you, which of our visions will claim uswhich will we claimhow will we go on livinghow will we touch, what will we knowwhat will we say to each other.\n\n- Adrienne\n|\nTongues in trees, books in running brooks, sermons in stones, and good in everything.\n\n- William\n|\nMy first-year mentor Leslie taught me that the hurrieder we go, the behinder we get.\n\n- Weam Namou, Healing Wisdom for a Wounded World: My Life-Changing Journey Through a Shamanic School: Book 1\n|\nLet us learn how to show our friendship for a man when he is alive and not after he is dead' he suggested, 'After that my own rule is to let everything alone'.\n\n- F. Scott Fitzgerald, The Great Gatsby\n|\nA prince must not have any other object nor any other thought… but war, its institutions, and its discipline; because that is the only art befitting one who commands.\n\n- Niccolò Machiavelli, The Prince\n|\nThe book is a film that takes place in the mind of the reader. That's why we go to movies and say, 'Oh, the book is better.\n\n- Paulo\n|\nPeople have forgotten this truth,' the fox said. 'But you mustn’t forget it. You become responsible forever for what you’ve tamed. You’re responsible for your rose.\n\n- Antoine de Saint-Exupéry, The Little Prince\n|\nIf what you seek is Truth, there is one thing you must have above all else.” “I know. An overwhelming passion for it.” “No. An unremitting readiness to admit you may be wrong.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nIf you want to be happy, you need to set your mind on happiness.\n\n- Ana\n|\nPoetry must be as new as foam, and as old as the rock.\n\n- Ralph\n|\nKatsa and Po were trying to drown each other and, judging from their hoots of laughter, enjoying it immensely.\n\n- Kristin Cashore, Bitterblue\n|\nOne of George H. W. Bush's early teachers at Andover wrote, 'At the moment he is intellectually immature for his powers of reasoning are not entirely developed.\n\n- H.W.\n|\nReligion without reason is merely an illusion of religion – it is a mockery of religion, like it has become today.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Illusion of Religion: A Treatise on Religious Fundamentalism\n|\nIf someone isn't what others want them to be, the others become angry.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist\n|\nI could die for you. But I couldn't, and wouldn't, live for you.\n\n- Ayn Rand, The Fountainhead\n|\nMy true-love hath my heart and I have his, By just exchange one for the other given: I hold his dear, and mine he cannot miss; There never was a bargain better driven.\n\n- Philip Sidney, The Poems of Sir Philip Sidney\n|\nAs far as I’m concerned, eighteen holes of golf is the only happiness that money can buy. - Momofuku Ando\n\n- Andy\n|\nOnce war becomes a clash of absolutes, there is no breathing room for mercy. Absolute truth is blind truth.\n\n- Deepak Chopra, The Third Jesus: The Christ We Cannot Ignore\n|\nWhen life hands you a lemon, say, 'Oh yeah, I like lemons! What else ya got?